NORTH-WEST – A doctor from Ikageng, Potchefstroom, has been arrested for sexual assault for allegedly fondling and penetrating a patient in is surgery. The 20 year old woman had gone to the doctor for treatment when the 43 year old man allegedly fondled her breasts and also penetrated her with his fingers. According to the police, the 20-year old female complainant said she wasn't feeling well on September 5 and asked a neighbour to accompany her to a local doctor. She said she was taken into a consultation room alone where she told the doctor she had a headache, Her blood pressure was taken and the doctor asked if she preferred pills or an injection; she opted for the latter. Allegations are that the doctor started to massage her neck and breasts. He allegedly then asked her to lift her hands and massaged her genitals. While massaging the woman's genitals, the doctor allegedly penetrated her with his fingers, causing her to jump away from him. Police said when he asked her if she had experienced pain, she said she had and immediately left the room the went to the police station to lay a charge against the doctor. Ikageng police spokeswoman, Sergeant Kelebogile Trom, said the 43-year old doctor was arrested on September 10 on a sexual assault charge and was released on bail. She said investigations were ongoing. Sources close to the doctor said his surgery was still fully functional and open. This is not the first time a medical practitioner from Ikageng has faced trouble with the law. Earlier this year general practitioner Dr David Gaotingwe Sello had his license suspended following botched surgeries at his consulting rooms. – Health-e News.